x4freetext: - same 24Mg+n data are given
7 MV cn Van de Graaff accelerator of the
Hahn-Meitner-Institut Berlin, run at 6.3 MeV and
1 uA current.
Bombardement of a thick quartz target by a deuteron-
beam (1ns wide at 10E+06 pps) gave 2x10E+03 neutrons
per second for a solid angle of 2x10E-5 Sr.
Target-in-target-out runs together with
conventional time-of-flight technique.
Calibration with the gamma-lines, produced by the
deuterons in the target.
The flight path was 17.50 m between neutron-source
and detector.
The integrated beam current and the neutron
counting rate in a detector placed at 30. degr. lab
angle were used for normalization. The relative
agreement between the two monitors was better than 1%.
NE213 liquid scintillator (4in. diameter x
1 in. thick) on a VALVO XP1040 photomultiplier.
Transmission measurement.
For scattered neutrons from the experimental
environment.
For time-dependent variations of the neutron energy
distribution.
Erroneous electronic data collection and conversion.
Systematic error estimated to 1% for 24-Mg
and 2% for 14-N.
Energy resolution 20 keV at 4MeV.
Statistical error
Data taken from report.
Since table gave only energy increments, those have
been converted to absolute energy points,
corressponding to the data points, at CCDN.
